----
**[[#DDU]]SET device: condition [,condition]**

This form of the SET command configures an RT-11 device driver.

**ddu:**    
  The name of an installed device.
  The system selects the matching device driver.
**Condition**       
  The name of a condition to modify and an optional value.
  Device driver condition names may not be abbreviated.
* RUST records device driver settings in a data block appended to the driver image.
* Distributed RUST drivers already have the block appended.
* For other drivers RUST extends the driver image when the first SET operation is applied.
* The driver should be reinstalled after the first SET operation.
* See the [[Show_Command#DRIVER|SHOW DRIVER]] command and the [[DRIVER_Utility|DRIVER]] utility.

----
**SET BASIC ALL|BASIC|NONE**[[#BASIC]]

Selects the default functions for BASIC.

[[code format="text"]]
  ALL:    Selects all BASIC functions. The default.
  BASIC:  BASIC prompts you for the required functions.
  NONE:   Selects no BASIC functions.
[[code]]
----
**SET CLOCK 50_HERTZ|60_HERTZ**[[#CLOCK]]

Set your system clock to the local frequency.

[[code format="text"]]
  50_HERTZ:       Specifies 50 Hertz clock rate. The RUST default.
  60_HERTZ:       Specifies a 60 Hertz clock rate. The RT-11 default.
[[code]]
* This command should be only used in the system startup command file.
* RUST/SJ determines the clock frequency automatically during boot.
* RUST/XM adopts the frequency of the host system when it bootstraps.

----
**SET DEBUG**[[#DEBUG]]
**SET NODEBUG (default)**

Enable or disable the interactive debugger.

[[code format="text"]]
  SET DEBUG               ! Enable debugger
  SET NODEBUG             ! Disable debugger (default)
[[code]]
*For more information see the [[DB_Driver|DB]] driver.

----
**SET DEFAULT device**[[#DEFAULT]]

  Define the default disk and/or directory.

**Device**
  A device or directory specification.
  ".." specifies an up-directory operation.

Examples:
[[code format="text"]]
  .set default du0:       ! DU0: is the default
  .set default du3:\data\ ! DU3:\DATA\ is the default
  .set default ..         ! DU3: is the default
[[code]]
* RUST/XM LOGIN sets the initial default directory.
* Same as the CD command.

----
**SET DRIVER file item-list**[[#DRIVER]]

  Invokes the DRIVER utility to configure a device handler.

**File**
 Is the file name of a driver (not the device name)    
**Item-list**
 A set of device-driver configuration items    

----
**SET [NO]EDIT [EDIT|K52|KED|KEX|KEYPAD|TECO]**[[#EDIT]]

Configures command line editing and the default text editor.

Command line editing:

[[code format="text"]]
  SET EDIT        Enables command line editing.
  SET NOEDIT      Disables command line editing.
[[code]]
Default editor:

[[code format="text"]]
  Editor          Screen          Initial Default
  ------          ------          ---------------
  SET EDIT EDIT   Hardcopy/GT40
  SET EDIT K52    VT52
  SET EDIT KED    VT102           RT-11/SJ and RT-11/FB
  SET EDIT KEX    VT102           RT-11/XM
  SET EDIT KEYPAD VT102/VT200     RUST
  SET EDIT TECO   Hardcopy/VT102
[[code]]
* TECO VT102 mode fails under RUST/SJ because of memory space.
