**SET ERROR condition**[[#ERROR]]

Specifies the error level necessary to abort command files.
[[code format="text"]]
  SET ERROR ERROR    Aborts a command file if an Error occurs. The default.
  SET ERROR FATAL    Aborts a command file if a Fatal error occurs.
  SET ERROR NONE     Disables command file aborts except for Unconditional errors.
  SET ERROR SEVERE   Aborts a command file if a Severe error occurs.
  SET ERROR WARNING  Aborts a command file if a Warning occurs.
[[code]]
* See also [[Set_Command#STATUS|SET STATUS]] and [[Show_Command#CONFIG|SHOW CONFIG]].

